bug.short_desc: The attached report design is clipped when export report as PDF[1200]

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86078 report design
Description: Preview the attached report design in web viewer, then export report as pdf. The result is clipped.
Build version:2.3.0.v20080103-0800
Steps to reproduce: 1.Get the attached report design, which contains a crosstab. 2.Preview the report in web viewer, then export report as pdf.
Actual result: The pdf is clipped.
was fit-to-page set to true as default for PDF export?
Using the default setting-"Actual size" in the export report dialog.

This is the expected result.
By default, 1. if previewing a report directly in PDF, the render option is set to FIT_TO_PAGE. 2. if exporting the report as PDF from web viewer, the default setting is "actual size", which means the contents will keep their original size, so anything exceeding the page boundary will be clipped. To avoid the report being clipped, please choose "Fit to whole page".
